text: left Meteren () is a village in the Dutch province of Gelderland. It is a part of the municipality of West Betuwe, and lies about 10 km west of Tiel. The village Meteren has a population of around 3210.Statistics Netherlands (CBS), Statline: Kerncijfers wijken en buurten 2003-2005. As of 1 January 2005. The statistical area "Meteren", which also can include the surrounding countryside, has a population of around 3450. ==References== Category:Populated places in Gelderland Category:Geldermalsen
title: Meteren
